definition.value: An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of O(3)-(poly[beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcA-(1->3)]-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcA-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Xyl)-L-serine residue
An alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc-yl group having beta-configuration at its point of attachment.

An alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc-yl group having beta-configuration at its point of attachment.
A mixture of fluorescein-5- and fluorescein-6-carbonyl groups, derived from the commercially available 5(6)-carboxyfluorescein isomeric mixture
An indole alkaloid cation that is the conjugate acid of (3R)-3-hydroxy-2,3-dihydrotabersonine, obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino group. Major species at pH 7.3.
An indole alkaloid cation that is the conjugate acid of (3R)-1,2-didehydro-3-hydroxy-2,3-dihydrotabersonine, obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino group. Major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any N-(12-oxojasmonyl)-L-alpha-amino acid.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of any N-(12-hydroxy-12-oxojasmonyl)-L-alpha-amino acid.
A commercially available mixture of 5-carboxyfluorescein and 6-carboxyfluorescein isomers. A fluorescent dye, it is commonly used as a tracer agent.
An N(2)-[(3R)-3-(acyloxy)acyl]-L-ornithine zwitterion in which the acyl chain is saturated at position 2; the major species at pH 7.3.
A univalent carboacyl group formed from 5-carboxyfluorescein.
A member of the class of resolvins that is (5Z,8Z,11Z,13E,15E)-icosapentaenoic acid which is substituted at positions 17 and 18 by hydroxy groups (the 17,18S stereoisomer).
An amino acid zwitterion resulting from the transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the side-chain amino group of any N(5)-methyl-N(2)-[(3R)-3-(acyloxy)acyl]-L-ornithine; major species at pH 7.3.
A univalent carboacyl group formed from 6-carboxyfluorescein.

An amino acid zwitterion resulting from the transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the side-chain amino group of any N(5),N(5)-dimethyl-N(2)-[(3R)-3-(acyloxy)acyl]-L-ornithine; major species at pH 7.3.
An amino-acid betaine obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any N(5),N(5),N(5)-trimethyl-N(2)-[(3R)-3-(acyloxy)acyl]-L-ornithine; major species at pH 7.3.
An amino acid zwitterion resulting from the transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the side-chain amino group of any N(2)-[(3R)-hydroxy-acyl]-L-ornithine; major species at pH 7.3.
A beta-lactone that is oxetan-2-one carrying two alkyl substituents at positions 3 and 4 with cis-stereochemistry.
L-idofuranose in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
An indolobenzazepine that is 5,6,7,12-tetrahydroindolo[3,2-d][1]benzazepine carrying an oxo substituent at position 6.
An organic heterotetracyclic compound that is 1,3-dihydro-2H-1-benzazepin-2-one which shares its 4-5 bond with the 3-2 bond of 5-nitro-1H-indole.

An epoxy fatty acid that is (7E,9E,11Z,14Z,16E)-icosa-7,9,11,14,16-pentaenoic acid carrying an epoxy group at position 5S and a hydroxy group at position 18S. It is an intermediate in resolvin E1 biosynthesis.
